to Deer Lake on time,

02:12.966 --> 02:17.503
<i>Narrator:</i>
<i>But now, the upstart company</i>
<i>is facing a worst case scenario</i>

02:17.505 --> 02:21.140
<i>as warming temperatures</i>
<i>have forced a closure</i>
<i>of an ice bridge</i>

02:21.142 --> 02:24.076
<i>on the only trail</i>
<i>into Deer Lake,</i>

02:24.078 --> 02:28.113
<i>bringing the mission</i>
<i>to a sudden halt.</i>

02:28.115 --> 02:30.249
<i>Darrell:</i>
<i>I've got two transformers</i>
<i>on this trailer</i>

02:30.251 --> 02:31.517
that need to be to Deer Lake

02:31.519 --> 02:33.752
so they can get their power
restored.

02:33.754 --> 02:39.791
<i>Snow crossing's not letting us</i>
<i>get this job done.</i>

02:39.793 --> 02:41.827
<i>Lisa:</i>
<i>It's starting to get</i>
<i>a little late now,</i>

02:41.829 --> 02:45.797
and uh, they're repairing
this ice bridge,

02:45.799 --> 02:48.767
and they can't let us cross
until it freezes up.

02:48.769 --> 02:52.871
<i>and water doesn't freeze in</i>
<i>warm temperatures very well.</i>

02:52.873 --> 02:54.940
(Whirring)

02:54.942 --> 02:56.575
<i>Darrell:</i>
<i>This is the biggest contract</i>
<i>we've had</i>

02:56.577 --> 02:58.577
for this company, this year.

02:58.579 --> 03:00.579
We need to get it done.

03:01.981 --> 03:03.815
Sittin' here ain't doin' it.

03:10.890 --> 03:15.194
<i>Narrator:</i>
<i>The ice bridge won't officially</i>
<i>be reopened until dawn.</i>

03:15.196 --> 03:18.230
<i>But with each passing minute,</i>
<i>the town's survival,</i>

03:18.232 --> 03:20.699
<i>and the fate of the business</i>
<i>are at stake.</i>

03:20.701 --> 03:22.234
(Engine hums)

03:23.870 --> 03:25.771
<i>Darrell:</i>
<i>I'm going crazy sittin' here.</i>

03:25.773 --> 03:27.873
We can't sit here all night.
I don't know what to do.

03:30.910 --> 03:33.145
<i>Copy, Lisa?</i>

03:33.147 --> 03:35.013
Yeah go ahead, Darrell.

03:35.015 --> 03:38.417
We need to get these
transformers to Deer Lake.

03:42.088 --> 03:44.489
Yeah, copy that.

03:44.491 --> 03:46.358
Are you ready to do this thing?

03:46.360 --> 03:50.028
Copy that. I'm grabbing
a gear right behind ya.

03:50.030 --> 03:51.630
<i>Lisa:</i>
<i>Then good to go.</i>

03:51.632 --> 03:53.832
Well, we're gonna go for it.

03:53.834 --> 03:55.234
(Shifting gears)

03:55.236 --> 03:59.504
<i>Narrator:</i>
<i>On "Ice Road Truckers."</i>

04:03.844 --> 04:08.113
♪

04:08.115 --> 04:12.384
<i>Mark:</i>
<i>It's taken years for me</i>
<i>to get to the top,</i>

04:16.657 --> 04:20.926
<i>Narrator:</i>
<i>Darryl and Lisa took on jobs</i>
<i>no one else would touch.</i>

04:20.928 --> 04:25.197
<i>Narrator:</i>
<i>But last week,</i>
<i>the new business owners</i>

04:25.199 --> 04:29.468
<i>Narrator:</i>
<i>Snagging the biggest</i>
<i>contract of the season.</i>

04:29.470 --> 04:33.739
I'm game.

04:38.012 --> 04:42.281
<i>on the only trail</i>
<i>into Deer Lake,</i>

04:42.283 --> 04:46.551
so they can get their power
restored.

04:50.824 --> 04:55.093
for this company, this year.

04:55.095 --> 04:59.364
<i>But with each passing minute,</i>
<i>the town's survival,</i>

04:59.366 --> 05:03.702
<i>Copy, Lisa?</i>

05:03.704 --> 05:07.973
<i>Lisa:</i>
<i>Then good to go.</i>

05:07.975 --> 05:12.244
<i>and the heavy loads</i>
<i>from the big rigs</i>

05:16.517 --> 05:28.493
♪

05:28.495 --> 05:32.764
Darell:
Yeah, let's rock 'n roll.

05:39.372 --> 05:42.007
<i>A little farther.</i>

05:42.009 --> 05:45.277
(Engine hums)

05:45.279 --> 05:46.611
I'm in.

05:50.416 --> 05:53.852
Yeah, I'm over the hump,
I'm right behind ya.

05:53.854 --> 05:55.420
Lisa:
Alrighty.

05:56.656 --> 05:59.591
<i>Darrell:</i>
<i>All right, hopefully that's</i>
<i>our last obstacle</i>

05:59.593 --> 06:02.327
<i>between here and Deer Lake.</i>

06:03.262 --> 06:07.666
<i>Lisa:</i>
<i>There's nothing we can do,</i>
<i>just keep going.</i>

06:07.668 --> 06:11.370
<i>Narrator:</i>
<i>With no time to waste, the team</i>
<i>drives through the night.</i>

06:11.372 --> 06:13.605
(Tires crunch on the snow)

06:18.511 --> 06:19.644
(Engine hums)

06:21.481 --> 06:23.682
<i>Lisa:</i>
<i>Almost to Deer Lake.</i>

06:23.684 --> 06:28.120
<i>Narrator:</i>
<i>Finally the town of Deer Lake</i>
<i>appears on the horizon.</i>

06:28.122 --> 06:29.654
Parking.

06:29.656 --> 06:31.022
(Airbrakes hiss)

06:31.024 --> 06:33.058
<i>Darrell:</i>
<i>This is the place!</i>

06:33.060 --> 06:36.862
<i>Narrator:</i>
<i>And Darrell and Lisa</i>
<i>come through.</i>

06:36.864 --> 06:38.463
Man: Hi! Nice to see ya.
Darrell: Darrell.

06:38.465 --> 06:39.765
Man: Yeah.
Lisa: Hi, Lisa.

06:39.767 --> 06:41.400
Jim:
Jim, Jim, hi, nice to meet ya,
Lisa.

06:41.402 --> 06:43.435
<i>Really glad you guys</i>
<i>made it in.</i>

06:43.437 --> 06:46.805
Narrator:
Delivering a vital haul
for a community in need.

06:46.807 --> 06:48.306
<i>Kim:</i>
<i>Those new transformers you</i>
<i>just brought in,</i>

06:48.308 --> 06:50.242
we will put them into service
immediately,

06:50.244 --> 06:53.011
and restore power
as soon as possible.

06:53.013 --> 06:56.047
<i>Darrell:</i>
<i>This was a huge score</i>
<i>for our company,</i>

06:56.049 --> 06:58.750
and it made a great
relationship with that
community,

06:58.752 --> 07:01.586
them knowing that
we brought them power.

07:01.588 --> 07:03.155
Again, I really appreciate
your efforts,

07:03.157 --> 07:04.689
and thank you very much for...

07:04.691 --> 07:05.657
Lisa: Thank you very much.
Jim: ...making the trip.

07:05.659 --> 07:07.392
Darrell:
Absolutely, meant a lot to us.

07:07.394 --> 07:09.428
Jim:
Meant a lot to us, too.

07:09.430 --> 07:11.029
<i>Lisa:</i>
<i>It's great that we made it</i>
<i>on time.</i>

07:11.031 --> 07:12.964
I was beginning to wonder
with all the obstacles,

07:12.966 --> 07:14.866
so I'm really glad
that we made it.

07:14.868 --> 07:16.067
We were able to pull through
for people

07:16.069 --> 07:17.736
and not let them down.

07:17.738 --> 07:20.672
Darrell: We have the power.
Lisa: We have the power.

07:20.674 --> 07:24.242
Darrell:
We do! We have the power!

07:24.244 --> 07:26.144
This company's tough
competition,

07:26.146 --> 07:27.846
so you'd better brace yourself,
Mark,

07:27.848 --> 07:29.080
because we're coming!

07:34.720 --> 07:38.457
<i>Narrator:</i>
<i>Back in Winnipeg,</i>
<i>at Polar headquarters,</i>

07:38.459 --> 07:41.460
<i>the competition's top dog</i>
<i>is reporting for duty.</i>

07:42.395 --> 07:44.162
Time to get back
on the ice roads

07:44.164 --> 07:46.164
and start doing some truckin'.

07:46.166 --> 07:48.266
Go see what old Mark
has to say.

07:48.268 --> 07:50.502
<i>Narrator:</i>
<i>Last week...</i>

07:51.704 --> 07:53.738
(Loud crash)
Holy (bleep)!

07:53.740 --> 07:56.141
<i>Blades just slid right off.</i>

07:56.143 --> 07:58.677
<i>Narrator:</i>
<i>A load of grader blades</i>
<i>for a government contract</i>

07:58.679 --> 08:00.345
<i>fell off Todd's trailer.</i>

08:00.347 --> 08:01.580
(Door shuts)

08:01.582 --> 08:03.982
Todd:
Oh, this sucks!

08:03.984 --> 08:06.818
<i>Narrator:</i>
<i>And to make sure Polar</i>
<i>made good on the delivery,</i>

08:06.820 --> 08:10.422
<i>he picked up the entire haul</i>
<i>by hand.</i>

08:10.424 --> 08:12.290
(Knocks)
Hey, hey, hey!

08:12.292 --> 08:13.191
What's up?

08:13.193 --> 08:14.593
Todd: Mark!
Mark: What's goin' on?

08:14.595 --> 08:16.094
Oh, I had a long run.

08:16.096 --> 08:17.762
Everything went pretty good.

08:17.764 --> 08:19.231
I pushed pretty hard
through there.

08:19.233 --> 08:20.999
I only had one little problem -

08:21.001 --> 08:22.834
I went around a corner
and all them (bleep)

08:22.836 --> 08:24.135
son of a bitch's
blades come off.

08:24.137 --> 08:26.771
But I got it all, you know I
hand-loaded them all back on,

08:26.773 --> 08:28.740
restrapped them back down,
retied them,

08:28.742 --> 08:31.776
got 'em there, got 'em
delivered, and got out. So...

08:31.778 --> 08:33.845
So you, you delivered
everything?

08:33.847 --> 08:34.813
Everything got, oh yeah,

08:34.815 --> 08:36.047
I mean, I got 'em all
picked up,

08:36.049 --> 08:37.349
and I even dug through the snow

08:37.351 --> 08:38.416
and made sure
they were all there.

08:38.418 --> 08:41.019
Yeah, yeah, hold on.
Did you count everything?

08:41.021 --> 08:42.354
Well, I didn't count 'em.

08:42.356 --> 08:44.022
Well, how do you know you
delivered everything?

08:44.024 --> 08:46.157
Because according
to this right here,

08:46.159 --> 08:49.094
three missing blades
for Tadoule Lake.

08:49.096 --> 08:50.795
Oh you're (bleep) me.

08:50.797 --> 08:53.965
No, I'm serious.
Three missing blades.

08:53.967 --> 08:55.534
No, no (bleep) way.

08:55.536 --> 08:57.168
And they weren't even where
you were telling me.

08:57.170 --> 08:58.870
They were at the start
of the winter road,

08:58.872 --> 09:01.072
and they found 'em.
They're in Lynn Lake.

09:01.074 --> 09:03.008
The highways guys in Lynn Lake
have 'em.

09:03.010 --> 09:06.177
So you dropped them at the
start of the winter road,

09:06.179 --> 09:08.547
and then at the end.

09:08.549 --> 09:10.048
You know what, Todd,
I can't have this.

09:10.050 --> 09:12.150
This is-this is an important
contract for me.

09:12.152 --> 09:14.553
This is a government contract
I'm vying for,

09:14.555 --> 09:15.654
they've got three missing
blades,

09:15.656 --> 09:18.123
we've gotta fix this.

09:18.125 --> 09:20.025
It's not a phone call anybody
ever wants to get,

09:20.027 --> 09:23.061
when a driver loses freight
on the road.

09:23.063 --> 09:26.731
I was mortified.
I didn't want to get that call.

09:26.733 --> 09:28.567
I mean, Todd, under normal
circumstances

09:28.569 --> 09:29.868
I'd probably send you in
a half-tonne truck

09:29.870 --> 09:33.872
to go deliver them on your
own dime, and on your own time.

09:33.874 --> 09:35.440
But, you know lucky for you,

09:35.442 --> 09:37.609
I've got another load that's
got to go to Tadoule,

09:37.611 --> 09:38.877
but I need you to make
this right.

09:38.879 --> 09:40.512
I need you to pick up those
blades in Lynn Lake

09:40.514 --> 09:42.647
and get those blades as fast
as you can,

09:42.649 --> 09:43.982
and get 'em up there.

09:43.984 --> 09:45.350
Oh, I'm going to make it right,
believe me.

09:45.352 --> 09:47.886
All right, bud.

09:47.888 --> 09:50.589
<i>Mark:</i>
<i>The one run that I really</i>
<i>needed for him to get done,</i>

09:50.591 --> 09:52.624
<i>he loses some freight.</i>

09:52.626 --> 09:55.694
Totally not like Todd,
but nonetheless, uh...

09:56.896 --> 09:59.497
driver responsibility,
driver error.

09:59.499 --> 10:02.534
<i>Todd:</i>
<i>It is my responsibility to take</i>
<i>care of this situation.</i>

10:02.536 --> 10:05.804
<i>Narrator:</i>
<i>Because of Todd's mistake,</i>
<i>Polar could lose the government</i>

10:05.806 --> 10:08.340
<i>as a new customer.</i>

10:08.342 --> 10:10.442
<i>And with hundreds</i>
<i>of miles ahead,</i>

10:10.444 --> 10:15.447
<i>he's got a long way to go to</i>
<i>keep the contract on track.</i>

10:15.449 --> 10:17.349
<i>Todd:</i>
<i>I felt like I let Mark down</i>

10:17.351 --> 10:19.150
because he had stressed
to me on how important

10:19.152 --> 10:20.885
this government contract was.

10:20.887 --> 10:22.387
<i>I was disappointed in myself.</i>

10:22.389 --> 10:25.523
Locked and loaded!

10:25.525 --> 10:28.893
Look out Tadoule Lake,
here we come again!

10:28.895 --> 10:31.296
<i>Who knows what's gonna</i>
<i>happen this time.</i>

10:36.235 --> 10:38.637
<i>Narrator:</i>
<i>Deep in Manitoba...</i>

10:38.639 --> 10:40.872
(Engine hums)

10:40.874 --> 10:42.207
Right now I just wanna
get into Lynn Lake,

10:42.209 --> 10:43.742
I'm damn near there.

10:43.744 --> 10:47.012
<i>Mark is, you know of course</i>
<i>he's all over me.</i>

10:47.014 --> 10:48.513
(Engine hums)

10:48.515 --> 10:52.317
<i>Narrator:</i>
<i>Todd Dewey's on a mission</i>
<i>for redemption.</i>

10:54.120 --> 10:58.356
