get a visual on 'em.

11:06.565 --> 11:10.735
<i>All right, at the fuel dock</i>
<i>in Lynn Lake.</i>

11:10.737 --> 11:14.572
This is where they said
they were gonna drop off
these blades.

11:14.574 --> 11:17.175
<i>Yeah, son of a bitch,</i>
<i>that's those right there.</i>

11:17.177 --> 11:19.577
(Airbrakes hiss,
door shuts)

11:21.313 --> 11:23.782
This is it,
just three little plates.

11:23.784 --> 11:26.084
This is what fell off,
can you frickin' believe it?

11:26.086 --> 11:28.420
I can't believe it.

11:32.525 --> 11:34.459
<i>Those ain't coming out</i>
<i>of there.</i>

11:34.461 --> 11:35.994
Rock 'n roll.

11:35.996 --> 11:37.696
<i>Narrator:</i>
<i>The stray blades</i>
<i>are loaded up,</i>

11:37.698 --> 11:40.932
<i>but Todd's day</i>
<i>is far from over.</i>

11:42.435 --> 11:44.969
<i>It's still another 200 miles</i>
<i>to Tadoule Lake</i>

11:44.971 --> 11:48.673
<i>before the job is complete.</i>

11:48.675 --> 11:52.077
Leaving Lynn Lake,
on our way to Tadoule Lake.

11:52.079 --> 11:54.212
Grader blades are picked up,

11:54.214 --> 11:57.849
<i>everybody can leave me alone</i>
<i>about these dumb ass grader</i>
<i>blades.</i>

11:57.851 --> 12:03.722
<i>Narrator:</i>
<i>As Todd looks to keep a</i>
<i>government contract alive</i>
<i>for Polar...</i>

12:03.724 --> 12:05.323
<i>back at headquarters,</i>

12:05.325 --> 12:07.559
(Backing up beeps)

12:10.463 --> 12:13.331
Art:
Surprise, surprise!

12:13.333 --> 12:16.601
<i>Narrator:</i>
<i>The company's wild card is</i>
<i>getting back on the road.</i>

12:19.438 --> 12:21.172
<i>Art:</i>
<i>We'll have to watch out</i>
<i>for this.</i>

12:21.174 --> 12:22.607
(Crash)

12:22.609 --> 12:23.675
Whoa!

12:23.677 --> 12:25.110
<i>Narrator:</i>
<i>Last week...</i>

12:25.112 --> 12:27.579
What the (bleep) is goin' on
now?

12:27.581 --> 12:30.348
<i>Narrator:</i>
<i>An oil leak abruptly</i>
<i>ended Art's run.</i>

12:30.350 --> 12:31.483
Art:
How you doin', Mark?

12:31.485 --> 12:33.118
We're sittin' on the side
of the road up here, boy.

12:33.120 --> 12:34.953
The oil light keeps coming on.

12:34.955 --> 12:37.388
<i>Narrator:</i>
<i>He missed out</i>
<i>on a big paycheque.</i>

12:37.390 --> 12:39.491
<i>Art:</i>
<i>How the (bleep) am I supposed</i>
<i>to make any money like this?</i>

12:40.993 --> 12:42.427
(Knocks)
Mark: Hey!

12:42.429 --> 12:44.028
Art: How you doin', Mark, boy?
Mark: What's happenin'?

12:44.030 --> 12:46.297
